Class Coords

  • java.lang.Object
    • Coords

  • public class Coords
extends java.lang.Object
    Class file that generates Cartesian coordinates for use in storing x and y values of points found on a user-defined circle. A default constructor sets the values of the instance variables, x and y, to 0. If two doubles are passed in, another constructor stores the first number in x and the second in y.
    Since:
    Spring 2016
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
